This topic lists the parameters that are used to collect and send data with 
Pivotal Telemetry Collector.

## <a id="collect"></a>Collect

To collect data with Pivotal Telemetry Collector you configure the following 
parameters:

<table class="nice">

    <th>Flag</th>
    <th>Description</th>
    
    <tr>
      <td><code>output-dir</code></td>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li><code>$OUTPUT_DIR</code></li>
          <li>string</li>
          <li>Local directory where the command writes the output <code>tar</code> 
          file</li></ul></td>
    </tr>
    
    <tr>
      <td><code>url</code></td>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li><code>$OPS_MANAGER_URL</code></li>
          <li>string</li>
          <li>Ops Manager URL where the command collects data from.</li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    
    <tr>
      <td><code>username</code></td>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li><code>$OPS_MANAGER_USERNAME</code></li>
          <li>string</li>
          <li>Ops Manager username</li>
          <li>Not required if you are using client authentication</li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    
    <tr>
      <td><code>password</code></td>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li><code>$OPS_MANAGER_PASSWORD</code></li>
          <li>string</li>
          <li>Ops Manager password</li>
          <li>Not required if you are using client authentication</li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    
    <tr>
      <td><code>client-id</code></td>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li><code>$OPS_MANAGER_CLIENT_ID</code></li>
          <li>string</li>
          <li>Ops Manager client ID</li>
          <li>Not required if you are using the <code>username</code> and 
          <code>password</code> parameters for authentication</li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    
    <tr >
      <td><code>client-secret</code></td>
        <td>
          <ul>
            <li><code>$OPS_MANAGER_CLIENT_SECRET</code></li>
            <li>string</li>
            <li>Ops Manager client secret</li>
            <li>Not required if you are using the <code>username</code> and 
            <code>password</code> for authentication</li>
          </ul>
        </td>
    </tr>
    
    <tr>
      <td><code>env-type</code></td>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li><code>$ENV_TYPE</code></li>
          <li>string</li>
          <li>The type of environment you are using to collect data</li>
          <li>You can enter one the following options:
            <ul>
              <li>development</li>
              <li>qa</li> 
              <li>pre-production</li> 
              <li>production</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    
    <tr>
      <td><code>insecure-skip-tls-verify</code></td>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li><code>insecure-skip-tls-verify</code></li>
          <li>Skips TLS validation on HTTP requests to Ops Manager</li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
    
    <tr>
      <td><code>ops-manager-timeout</code></td>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li>int</li>
          <li>Timeout in seconds for Ops Manager HTTP requests</li>
          <li>Defaults to 30</li>
          </ul></td>
    </tr>
        
</table>

## <a id="send"></a>Send

To send data with Pivotal Telemetry Collector you configure the following 
parameters:

<table class="nice">

<th>Flag</th>
<th>Meaning</th>

<tr>
<td><code>path</code></td>
<td>
  <ul>
    <li>string</li>
    <li>Path to the <code>FoundationDetails.tar</code> file written by the 
    <code>collect</code> command</li></ul>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
  <td><code>api-key</code></td>
  <td>
    <ul>
      <li><code>$API_KEY</code></li>
      <li>string</li>
      <li>Key used to authenticate with the Pivotal Telemetry API</li>
      <li>Provided to customers by Pivotal</li>
    </ul>
  </td>
</tr>

</table>
